### ============================================================
### Smoke test do fluxo de upload em chunks
###
### Uso:
###   1. Sobe a infra:        docker compose up -d
###   2. Sobe o app:          ./mvnw spring-boot:run
###   3. Cria o arquivo de teste (so 1 vez), no terminal da IDE:
###      [System.IO.File]::WriteAllBytes("chunk.bin", (New-Object byte[] 10MB))
###   4. Roda este arquivo de cima pra baixo, clicando no "Run" de cada bloco.
###      O uploadId da primeira chamada e capturado e reusado nas seguintes.
###
### IDEs que entendem .http:
###   - IntelliJ IDEA (HTTP Client embutido em Ultimate, plugin no Community)
###   - VS Code + extensao "REST Client" (Huachao Mao)
### ============================================================

### 1) Inicia o upload — cria o multipart no MinIO e a linha no Postgres.
###    O script handler abaixo guarda o uploadId em uma variavel global
###    pra reutilizar nos blocos seguintes.
POST http://localhost:8080/upload/init
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "filename": "test-file.bin",
  "totalChunks": 3
}

> {%
    client.global.set("uploadId", response.body.uploadId);
    client.log("uploadId capturado: " + response.body.uploadId);
%}

### 2) Envia o chunk 0 (10MB)
POST http://localhost:8080/upload/chunk/{{uploadId}}/0
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="chunk.bin"
Content-Type: application/octet-stream

< ./chunk.bin
--WebAppBoundary--

### 3) Envia o chunk 1
POST http://localhost:8080/upload/chunk/{{uploadId}}/1
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="chunk.bin"
Content-Type: application/octet-stream

< ./chunk.bin
--WebAppBoundary--

### 4) Envia o chunk 2 (ultimo) — apos esse, a UploadService publica
###    a mensagem no RabbitMQ e o UploadEventConsumer monta o arquivo final.
POST http://localhost:8080/upload/chunk/{{uploadId}}/2
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="chunk.bin"
Content-Type: application/octet-stream

< ./chunk.bin
--WebAppBoundary--

### 5) Consulta status — apos uns 1-2 segundos do bloco 4, deve estar COMPLETED.
###    Se ainda estiver PROCESSING, executa esse bloco de novo (a montagem e
###    assincrona via RabbitMQ).
GET http://localhost:8080/upload/status/{{uploadId}}